                   "message":  "MENUARC-DOC-RECONCILE-A3: reconcile A3 docs after the Play menu landed (#297)\n\nForward-only planning-substrate hygiene after #297 (6ea5006,\nMENUREGISTRY-PLAYMENU-A3) added the Play menu (Play/Pause/Stop/Step) via the\nW08 MenuRegistry. Prepends a new 2026-06-03 snapshot to Status.md + HANDOFF.md,\ninserts a new \"2026-06-03 - Play menu now registry-produced (#297 A3)\"\nsubsection into plans/BASELINE.md above the A2 subsection, and appends a\nmatching change.md entry. All A2/A1 snapshots, subsections, and entries are\nbyte-identical (pure prepend/insert/append - +21/-0).\n\nRecords that Play is no longer the deferred next beat: the host builds all\nthree menus from one MenuRegistry (file + edit + play points), and editor-shell\nroutes Command::PlayStart/PlayPause/PlayStop/PlayStep to handle_button. View is\nnow the lone remaining standard menu (it genuinely needs a new camera-reset\naction, so it is a feature beat, not pure wiring).\n\nDocs-only: no Rust source / test / Cargo / routing / rustdoc / lint-doc change\n(the menu rustdoc was already widened to File + Edit + Play inside #297 itself).\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (Markdown-only; no Rust touched).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
